This case was personal. I represented a close family member who waited over 8 years for justice. Our client’s business was being smeared, and was owed a substantial amount money for doing excellent construction work. This entire week was years of travel and hard work leading to justice for him and his family. The system worked this time. Our entire team put their hearts into this case and the result was everything we asked for. The jury wanted to award more after hearing all the facts and the lies from the defendants. After the case was over, the judge and jury sat down with us. This rarely happens. They all spoke very highly of the way we handled the case. We were blown away by their comments. This trial was also very special to me because our passion came out for helping people. So happy this special client obtained justice after waiting years for his day in court.
What a glorious day! A dream to watch a World Cup with my son. A dream to see Messi win it.

This is Shamieh Law’s version of a “happy hour.” No alcohol. Our “happy hour” included an intentional walk in nature connecting with our team outside the office, followed by a guided yoga practice by the king of yoga in dallas @sean_yogibeiers, and then a healthy lunch at the @thedallasarboretum. Our team had the rest of the day (in the middle of the week) to do whatever they wanted. Most businesses in the US wouldn’t do this. They are too laser focused on money. But what they are not seeing is employee morale is directly linked to efficiency, production, and profitability. It’s directly linked to realizing that as a business owner, we have a way bigger responsibility than just employing people and providing them with a salary. Our responsibility includes educating mental health, emphasizing wellness, providing a strong work - life balance and making sure each team member feels appreciated for how hard they work. If you own a business, I encourage you to regularly copy exactly what we did today and see how your employee morale, your own happiness, and your profitability starts to increase. The more you give, the more you receive.

Organic Fruits and Nuts. These are some of the healthy snacks we offer our team. No more junk food. No more fast food or soda drinks in the office. If team members want fast food or soda drinks, they can still have them but not in the office. This is just one of the ways we are trying to elevate our employees’ lives.

We are very excited to announce that we will be moving into our new home in uptown Dallas very soon! This home feels just right. That’s the only way this move works. I’ve asked every employee to write down an intention of what this home will provide our employees, their families, our clients, and the community at large. We will use these intentions along with all the opportunities/blessings this home provides us to serve our clients, grow as individuals and as a collective law firm, and give back to our community to make DFW a better place to live. Service. Growth. Giving back. That’s our future in this home.

Coach Robinson is a former client and a dear friend. He coached high school football at DeSoto High and coached some of the best teams in Texas. We have had the privilege of representing him, his daughters, and his in-laws. He is family. He doesn’t know we are posting this and didn’t ask for our help but he needs all of our help. If you are willing and able, please watch the ABC interview of him and donate to his cause. His story is beautiful and it’s just getting started. Go Fund Me and interview in bio.

Since 1999, the US has given approximately $3 BILLION a year to Israel in military aid. $3 BILLION A YEAR! Since 1946, the US has given over $315 BILLION to Israel in aid. Imagine where that money could have been used in America: Education, healthcare, our veterans, the homeless, or our food quality. What nonsense reason are we told to support Israel? To secure peace and stability in the region? It doesn’t look like the “plan” is working. The real reason the US is so one-sided with Israeli funding is military / political pressure and political donations to US elected officials. AIPAC is an Israeli lobbyist group in the US and one of the most influential in the entire country. I added a link in the bio showing how much money pro-Israel groups donate. The numbers are astonishing. US politicians were given approx. $43 million in 2022. It becomes much easier to understand that if you are a power hungry politician and a lobbyist group gives you enough money that changes your life, you may feel obligated to repay the favor in the form of blindly supporting whatever they want. This conflict isn’t about right vs wrong, Jew vs. Arab (Christians and Muslims), one side vs. another, anti-Semitic vs. pro-Semitic, them vs. us. So many well-respected Jews have come forward recently and strongly spoke out against the Israeli gov. They understand the root cause of this conflict is greed and an endless occupation driving a small minority of Palestinians to extreme measures. I’ll never condone violence. The only side I choose is humanity, and I understand that most gov’s are using us as pawns to divide us. We are easily controlled when divided. They attempt to brainwash us through propaganda to force us to pick a side and rationalize the killing of thousands of people. You can love Israelis & Palestinians, desire peace & basic human rights for all, and at the same time be critical of American foreign policy, the Israeli government, & condemn Hamas. But peace will never be achieved until the occupation is ended. If you don’t believe the occupation exists, maybe it’s time to hold your opinion on the conflict until you have seen it in person. Once you see, you can’t unsee.
